modules.description: This module defines core signatures for portable components in MirageOS, including time, clocks, endpoints, consoles, block devices, key/value stores, and filesystems. It specifies the required operations for each abstraction, such as reading from a console, writing to a block device, or retrieving values from a store. Concrete use cases include building and composing OS components like network stacks, storage backends, and device drivers in a modular and portable way.
